Nasarawa United Football Club of Lafia has fixed Wednesday, September 16th, 2020, as the resumption date for its players and officials. This, the club said is in line with the lifting of embargo on sporting activities across Nigeria by the Presidential Taskforce on COVID-19 and complying with the League Management Company’s (LMC) fixing of September 18 as the commencement date for the submission of players’ licensing applications for the 2020/2021 Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) Season. Chairman of the club, Barr. Isaac Danladi, who disclosed this at the end of the club’s management meeting yesterday in Lafia, said the resumption date became imperative to adequately prepare the team for the next football season. He revealed that the Nasarawa State government, under the leadership of Governor Abdullahi Sule has procured a multi-million-naira edifice for the club to serve as administrative office and camp house for the officials and players respectively. Danladi added that in order to make the present camp house and stadium facilities habitable in tandem with the COVID-19 protocols, the management had directed that it should be fumigated accordingly. While thanking Governor Sule and the government of Nasarawa State for the great gesture in procuring the edifice, the club chairman, who also doubles as the chairman of the NPFL Club Owners’ Association (COA) equally revealed that the club has retained thirty-five (35) players ahead of the new league season.